span.span: SENIOR RECOGNITION

1). Since the yearbook staff was only able to take one set of group pictures of the seniors and the cap and gown pictures were not able to be taken, we are asking all senior parents to take a picture of your graduate in his/her cap and gown, and email it to Mrs Vatthauer prior to May 15th. Mail the digital picture to: lvatthauer@rlfedu.org

2). Buy a recognition ad in honor of your favorite graduate(s). Ads are $10 for notes only; $15 for a picture and a note. Deadline for purchase of recognition ads is May 15, 2020. Click to get your copy of the form.
J.A. Hughes Elementary School
J.A. HUGHES EAGLE WAY!
BE KIND to everyone and everything.
WORK HARD. Always do your best.
BELONG. Accept others and be a part of your school family.

J.A. Hughes Elementary School is part of the Red Lake Falls School District and located in Red Lake Falls, MN. We are a growing Preschool-6th grade school with primarily two sections per grade level. Students at J.A. Hughes benefit from the Board of Education’s commitment to a low student-to-teacher ratio. This commitment allows us to provide a safe and caring environment focusing on both the academic and social-emotional needs of students. We work each day to promote the J.A. Hughes Eagle Way: Be Kind – To everyone and everything. Work Hard- Always do your best. Belong- Accept others and be a part of your school family.
Lafayette High School
LAFAYETTE HIGH SCHOOL CORE VALUES:
BE INVESTED • Dream, Plan, Do.
BE ACCOUNTABLE • Own your choices.
BE RESPECTFUL • Demonstrate kindness through words and actions.
BE EXCELLENT • Are you the Hardest Worker?
BE A LEADER - We challenge students to achieve something every day and to believe - I Can, I Will and I Did!
Lafayette High School is located in a rural community with approximately 1700 residents and is an oasis in Northwest Minnesota situated between the Clearwater and Red Lake Rivers.

With approximately 170 students in grades 7-12, students and teachers have the benefit of small class sizes. Lafayette has implemented 1:1 learning with the implementation of Chrome-books for each student. The school has implemented the college and career readiness program, Ramp Up to Readiness, for all students in order to help better prepare them for life after Lafayette.
JA Hughes Elementary School
601 1st Street, NE
P.O. Box 7
Red Lake Falls, MN 56750
Phone Number : 253-2161
Independent School District #630 is an equal opportunity provider and employer
